===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|rædan|rǣdan|advise, read|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|raedanan|advise, counsel|lang=en}}. Cognate with Dutch {{term|raden|lang=nl}}, German {{term|raten|lang=de}}, Swedish {{term|råda|lang=sv}}. The development from ‘advise, interpret’ to ‘interpret letters, read’ is unique to English. Compare {{term|rede}}.

